   "source": [
    "# Group age according to their age groups \n",
    "group = [\n",
    "        (df['Age']<3), \n",
    "        (df['Age'] >= 3) & (df['Age'] < 17),\n",
    "        (df['Age'] >= 17) & (df['Age'] < 31),\n",
    "        (df['Age'] >= 31) & (df['Age'] < 45),\n",
    "        (df['Age'] >= 45)\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "category = ['Babies', 'Children', 'Young adults', 'Middle-age adults', 'Old adults']\n",
    "\n",
    "df['Categories'] = np.select(group, category)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "for i in ['Age', 'Destination', 'Distribution Channel', 'Agency Type', 'Agency']: \n",
    "    # Compute cross tabulation table \n",
    "    cross_df_age_default = pd.crosstab(df[i],df['Claim'])\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Compute chi-square contigency test \n",
    "    chi_square_stats, p_value, degree_of_freedom, expected = chi2_contingency(cross_df_age_default)\n",
    "\n",
    "    alpha = 0.05\n",
    "    print(f\"Chi-square test of {i} and Claim\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Chi-sq-value: {chi_square_stats:.3f}\\np-value: {p_value:.4g}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if p_value <= alpha:\n",
    "        # If p-value less than alpga then reject H0\n",
    "        print(f\"There is a significant relation between {i} and travel insurance claim\\n\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Else do not reject H0\n",
    "        print(f\"No relation between {i} and travel insurance claim\\n\")"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Plot 8: Top 20 travel destinations for the most claimed travel insurance\n",
    "\n",
    "total = df['Destination'].value_counts().to_frame()    # Frequency count for destination in overall\n",
    "claimy = df_y['Destination'].value_counts().to_frame()     # Frequency count for destination when there is a claim \n",
    "df_claim = pd.concat([total, claimy], axis=1).reset_index()    # Create a dataframe \n",
    "df_claim.columns = ['country', 'total', 'claimed']    # Rename columns \n",
    "df_claim['percentage'] = (df_claim['claimed']/ df_claim['total'])*100    # Compute the percentage \n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot a bar plot for the top 20 travel destinations for the most claimed travel insurance\n",
    "sns.barplot(y='country', \n",
    "            x='percentage',\n",
    "            data=df_claim.sort_values(\"percentage\", ascending=False)[:20]).set(title='Top 20 travel destination for the most claimed travel insurance'); "
   ]
